    <h2>What Is Canva?</h2>
    <p>Canva is a cloud-based graphic design platform that lets anyone create stunning visuals — from social media posts and presentations to logos and videos. What started as a simple drag-and-drop tool has evolved into a design powerhouse with serious AI features baked in.</p>
    <p>With over <strong>150 million monthly active users</strong>, Canva has become the go-to design tool for marketers, social media managers, small business owners, and anyone who needs professional-looking graphics without hiring a designer.</p>

    <h2>Our Testing Process</h2>
    <p>We used Canva's AI features for 2 full weeks on real projects:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>20 social media posts (Instagram, LinkedIn, Facebook)</li>
      <li>5 presentation decks</li>
      <li>10 AI-generated images using Canva's Magic Media</li>
      <li>5 logo concepts</li>
      <li>3 short video edits using Canva's video tools</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We tested both the free plan and Canva Pro to give you a complete picture.</p>

    <h2>Key AI Features</h2>

    <h3>1. Magic Design</h3>
    <p>Magic Design is Canva's flagship AI feature. Upload an image or select a template, and AI suggests designs, adjusts layouts, and applies consistent styling automatically. In our tests, it produced usable designs in <strong>under 30 seconds</strong>.</p>

    <h3>2. Magic Media (AI Image Generator)</h3>
    <p>Canva's AI image generator creates images from text prompts. While not as powerful as Midjourney or DALL-E, it's integrated directly into your designs — no export/import needed. Great for quick illustrations and concept art.</p>

    <h3>3. Magic Write (AI Copywriting)</h3>
    <p>Need headlines, captions, or body text? Magic Write generates copy based on your prompts. It's not replacing professional copywriters, but it's excellent for brainstorming and first drafts.</p>

    <h3>4. Canva's AI Background Remover</h3>
    <p>Remove backgrounds from any image with one click. Accuracy is impressive — it handled complex edges better than most dedicated tools. This alone is worth trying.</p>

    <h3>5. Brand Kits</h3>
    <p>Upload your brand colors, fonts, and logos. Canva applies them automatically across all designs, ensuring consistency. For teams, this is a game-changer.</p>

    <h3>6. AI Presentations</h3>
    <p>Describe what you need, and Canva generates a full presentation deck with matching slides, fonts, and imagery. We generated a 10-slide pitch deck in under 2 minutes.</p>

