    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <h3>Is Canva free?</h3>
    <p>Yes. Canva offers a free forever plan with access to 100K+ templates, basic design tools, and 1GB storage. No credit card required.</p>

    <h3>Is Canva Pro worth it?</h3>
    <p>Yes, if you need AI features like Magic Design, Magic Media (AI image generation), background remover, and Brand Kits. At $12.99/month, it's reasonably priced for the value.</p>

    <h3>Can Canva replace a graphic designer?</h3>
    <p>For most business needs, yes. Canva can handle social media posts, presentations, logos, and simple graphics. For complex branding or print work, you'll still need a professional designer.</p>

    <h3>How good is Canva's AI image generator?</h3>
    <p>Magic Media is good for quick illustrations and concept art. It's not as powerful as Midjourney or DALL-E 3, but it's integrated directly into your designs, which is convenient.</p>

    <h3>Can I use Canva for YouTube thumbnails?</h3>
    <p>Yes! Canva has dedicated YouTube thumbnail templates. Combined with Magic Design, you can create eye-catching thumbnails in minutes.</p>

    <h3>Does Canva work offline?</h3>
    <p>Limited. You can edit existing designs offline, but you need an internet connection to access templates, Magic AI features, and cloud storage.</p>

